00:35:19.540 --> 00:35:24.590
They have a tickling
robot which is controlled

00:35:24.590 --> 00:35:27.750
by the user with a joystick.

00:35:27.750 --> 00:35:30.310
So imagine with your right
hand you have the joystick

00:35:30.310 --> 00:35:31.930
and you can move it
in all directions

00:35:31.930 --> 00:35:36.790
and that controls the operation
of a tickle finger which is a,

00:35:36.790 --> 00:35:41.720
like a big sharp thing and
that tickles the opposite hand.

00:35:41.720 --> 00:35:47.060
Okay, so they did this
research in 3 scenarios;

00:35:47.060 --> 00:35:51.870
scenario 1 is the movement of
the joystick perfectly correlates

00:35:51.870 --> 00:35:54.460
with the movement of the
robotic tickle finger,

00:35:54.460 --> 00:35:59.360
so when you move the joystick
up the tickle finger goes up

00:35:59.360 --> 00:36:02.920
